(\mathbf{v_1+v_2}) \times (\mathbf{v_1+v_2}) = (\mathbf{v_1}\times \mathbf{v_1})+(\mathbf{v_1}\times \mathbf{v_2})+(\mathbf{v_2}\times \mathbf{v_1})+(\mathbf{v_2}\times \mathbf{v_2})
\end{align}

Consider the identity $\mathbf{v} \times \mathbf{v} = \mathbf{0}$ for the last 2 pieces on the right-hand side. We can easily simplify the problem and come out with \begin{align}
(\mathbf{v} \times \mathbf{v})+(\mathbf{v} \times  \mathbf{v})=(\mathbf{v \times v})= \mathbf{0}
\end{align}

The answer is $\boxed{ \mathbf{0}}$

